1. Introduction
Welcome to Bloom - Mood Tracker & Journal ("we," "our," "us," or the "App"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and handling any personal information we obtain from you with care and transparency. This Privacy Policy is designed to inform you about how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use the App.

2. Information We Collect
2.1 Personal Information
While Bloom is designed primarily as an offline productivity tool, we may collect limited information under certain circumstances, such as:

Information you voluntarily provide (e.g., when contacting customer support)

Device details (e.g., type of device, operating system)

Basic usage data and performance analytics (if analytics are enabled)

2.2 Non-Personal Information
We may collect non-identifiable information, such as:

Aggregated usage statistics

Anonymous interaction data

General demographic trends (not linked to any individual user)

3. How We Use Your Information
We may use the collected information to:

Operate, maintain, and improve the App

Respond to your messages, questions, or support requests

Analyze overall usage patterns and trends

Notify you of technical updates or support-related information

Prevent fraudulent activity and ensure compliance with legal requirements

4. Data Storage and Security
We take reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your data. However, no method of data transmission or electronic storage is entirely secure. You use the App and share data at your own risk.

5. Third-Party Services
Bloom - may include links to third-party websites or tools. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of such external services.

6. Children's Privacy
The App is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect any personal information from users under 13 years of age. If we learn that such data has been collected, we will delete it promptly.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may revise this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updates will be posted in the app or on the corresponding app store listing, and the "Last updated" date will reflect the most recent version. You are advised to review the policy regularly.

8. Your Rights
Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to access, correct, or request deletion of your personal data. Please contact us directly to make such a request.

9. Data Retention
We retain data only for as long as it is necessary for the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law.

10. International Data Transfers
Your data may be transferred to and stored in locations outside of your country or jurisdiction. By using the App, you consent to such transfers, even where local data protection laws may differ.

11. Contact Us
